cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques for noun phrase chunking in informal text. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses graphical models and semi-Markov conditional random fields, which are commonly used in machine learning and statistical modeling, suggesting that it could also fit into the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper also discusses the use of annotated corpora and empirical evaluations, which could place it in the sub-category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
